# {{context|UK|finance}} A small plastic card issued by a bank or similar which is a guarantee of payment of [[cheque]]s written by the cardholder (up to a specified maximum amount).  A business accepting a cheque card notes its number and is then assured of payment on the customer's cheque, ie. is protected against the cheque [[bounce|bouncing]].

